cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use these records in your research, please cite as below."
title: "Four world records in Grassmannian coherence packings (d=4, n=64) hlc"
abstract: >
  Four sub-Cohn world records for the minimum-coherence packing of 64 unit
  vectors in complex 4-dimensional space, obtained on May 12 and May 16, 2026,
  by an independent researcher running on a Mac M2 laptop single-thread.
  Records 1 and 2 (May 12) were produced by the Aquiles engine
  (smoothed-max + Riemannian gradient flow paradigm); Records 3 and 4
  (May 16) were produced by the Boagrius engine (constrained-feasibility
  paradigm) using cascade warmstarts. All four packings were verified
  byte-exact by five independent code paths. Record 2 was additionally
  reproduced byte-exact by Henry Cohn (MIT) within 43 minutes of notification.
  The cumulative gap from Record 4 to the previous Cohn record is
  approximately −1.263 × 10⁻⁴ (−0.0184%).
